Steve:
I finished reconstructing the graphseasrch rountines.  get the files from
my AI-programs/A-star directory.  A main purpose for me to do this 
is to show you how to do programming "right."

Note the differet layers of data abstraction:  the graphsearch part does
not assume any rep for list or node, neither state.  Likewise, node-access
part does not know how states are represented.  More importantly, 
if you first read graphsearch-info, you should know how to write it for a
different domain by only implementing a few functions.  Note I implemented
both 8puzzle and tower-of-honoi domains.  The domain dependent parts are 
in 8puzzle and tower.lisp, respectively.  Try to run them.

Please try to write a domain representation for blocks world domain, and 
think about how to change the program to IDA* search.

Have fun.

Qiang

